Q5.
Under what circumstances does a dismissal contravene the law?
A5.

Under the Employment Ordinance, dismissal in the following circumstances contravenes the law: dismissal of a female employee who has been confirmed pregnant and has served a notice of pregnancy to her employer; dismissal whilst the employee is on paid sick leave; dismissal by reason of an employee giving evidence or information in any proceedings or inquiry in connection with the enforcement of the Employment Ordinance, work accidents or breach of work safety legislation; dismissal of an employee for trade union membership and activities; or dismissal of an injured employee before having entered into an agreement with the employee for employee's compensation or before the issue of a certificate of assessment. Back to questions
